For the quail with bois boudran, cut the breasts off the quails, keeping the wing bone attached.Heat a griddle pan until hot and fry the quail breasts for 2-3 minutes on each side, or until cooked to your liking.Mix the remaining ingredients in a bowl until well combined and add the cooked quail. Stir until well combined.For the potato salad, boil the potatoes in a pan of boiling salted water for 5-8 minutes, or until tender. Drain.Mix the potatoes, olive oil, lemon juice and zest and basil in a bowl. Season, to taste, with salt and freshly ground black pepper.To serve, place two quail breasts onto of four serving plates. Spoon plenty of sauce on top and some potato salad alongside.